<abstract abstract-type="summary" id="ABS3">
<title>eTOC Blurb</title>
<p id="P6">Tiled radial glial cells (RGCs) provide an instructive template for the formation of the cerebral cortex. Memo1 regulates RGC tiling underlying radial unit formation and neuronal laminar organization. Mutations in <italic>MEMO1</italic> and resultant cortical malformations may contribute to autism risk.</p>
</abstract>
